item.content:encoded:
As a second year side project, i needed to produce a short documentary as part of my video editing module. This was hard because at this time i was flat out with my main group assignment which also happened to be a documentary (Click here to view). So myself and another member sat down and came up up with an idea that would involve telling a friends story. What made this relevant and interesting was the story itself. We had 3 weeks to plan, shot and edit the piece to hand and show.

 

Powerless. from Laidback Jay on Vimeo.

Response is a short documentary focused on the volunteers of the Drogheda River Rescue & Recovery, and Waterford Marine Search & Rescue. Both voluntary organisations strive to prevent people from entering the water and prevent suicide. These organisations aim to provide the best service they can, while receiving no government funding whatsoever.

Response - Short documentary

Response - Short Documentary (2016) from Laidback Jay

Some photography work

A gallery showcasing some of my photography and product design

In my 1st semester of 2nd year at ITB, i was tasked with doing a photoshoot involving a product. After some thinking i narrowed it down to two pieces, a watch and a bracelet. I tried a couple of techniques and decided i wanted to focus on a black and white with some kind of colour feature in it. After a couple of hours and a dozen test shots, this was my final piece.

"Beautiful design made simple with the power of Page Builder's pre-built layouts"
